By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Former Vice President, Atiku Abubakar has demanded a written retraction and apology from the Special Assistant to the President on Social Media, Lauretta Onochie over her libelous and defamatory publication against him. Atiku who wrote through his counsel, Mike Ozekhome, also
asked for a payment of N500, 000,000 (Five hundred million) as damages for the
false and malicious publication, insisted that the retraction must be published
in six national dailies circulating in Nigeria and one international daily as
well as on all the social media platforms, wherein the said defamatory
publication was made. The Special Assistant
to the President on Social Media, Lauretta Onochie had on 7th of May
2019, on her twitter handle page and also published globally online in the
social and other print media quoted as saying that:  “Atiku is on 
UAE watchlist – security sources. Security operatives in the United Arab
Emirates (UAE) are keeping a close tab on a former Nigerian Vice Pres Atiku
Abubakar who has been in the Middle East nation for several weeks now. What is
he doing there? Me: Shopping for Terrorists?” See full letter: